                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "The testbed described in Figure 2 is implemented using Commercial Off- The- Shelf (COS) devices. The agent is trained on a workstation equipped with an Intel i7- 8700 CPU, 32GB DDR4 RAM, an NVIDIA GeForce RTX 2060 GPU, and an Intel Wireless- AC 9560 Network Interface Card (NIC). The \"Receiver Application\" resides on a 4GB Raspberry Pi 4 Model B (RPi4B). The two AP used are a TP- Link EAP245 and a Netgear WAC505, connected to two Netgear GS108E switches. A 2015 Apple MacBook Pro with macOS Catalina v10.15.6 generates background traffic, which is sent to the receiving application running on a Dell Latitude 7000 laptop (E7470). Both the desktop machine and E7470 run the Ubuntu 20.04.5 LTS OS. All NIC- related optimizations, e.g., TCP Segmentation Offload (TSO) or Large Receive Offload"
                                }
